quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  17,70,We have honoured the sons of Adam and conveyed them on land and sea and provided them with good things and favoured them greatly over many We have created
  17,71,"On the Day We summon every people with their records, those who are given their Book in their right hand will read their Book and they will not be wronged by even the smallest speck"
  17,72,Those who are blind in this world will be blind in the Next World and even further off the Path
  17,73,"They were very near to enticing you away from some of what We have revealed to you, hoping that you would invent something against Us. Then they would have taken you as their intimate"
  17,74,"If We had not made you firm, you would have leaned towards them a little"
  17,75,Then We would have let you taste a double punishment in life and a double punishment in death. You would not have found any helper against Us
  17,76,They were very near to scaring you from the land with the object of expelling you from it. But had they done so they would only have remained there a short time after you
  17,77,That was the pattern with those We sent before you as Our Messengers. You will not find any changing of Our pattern
  17,78,"Establish salat from the time the sun declines until the darkening of the night, and also the recitation at dawn. The dawn recitation is certainly witnessed"
  17,79,And stay awake for prayer during part of the night as a supererogatory action for yourself. It may well be that your Lord will raise you to a Praiseworthy Station
  17,80,"Say: ´My Lord, make my entry sincere and make my leaving sincere and grant me supporting authority direct from Your Presence.´"
  17,81,"Say: ´Truth has come and falsehood has vanished. Falsehood is always bound to vanish.´"
  17,82,"We send down in the Qur´an that which is a healing and a mercy to the muminun, but it only increases the wrongdoers in loss"
  17,83,"When We bless man, he turns away and draws aside. When evil touches him, he despairs"
  17,84,"Say: ´Each man acts according to his nature, but your Lord knows best who is best guided on the Path.´"
  17,85,"They will ask you about the Ruh. Say: ´The Ruh is my Lord´s concern. You have only been given a little knowledge.´"
  17,86,If We wished We could take away what We have revealed to you and then you would not find any to guard you from Us —
  17,87,but for a mercy from your Lord. His favour to you is indeed immense
  17,88,"Say: ´If both men and jinn banded together to produce the like of this Qur´an, they could never produce anything like it, even if they backed each other up.´"
  17,89,"We have variegated throughout this Qur´an all kinds of examples for people, but most people spurn anything but kufr"
  17,90,"They say, ´We will not believe you until you make a spring gush out from the earth for us"
  17,91,or have a garden of dates and grapes which you make rivers come pouring through
  17,92,"or make the sky, as you claim, fall down on us in lumps; or bring Allah and the angels here as a guarantee"
  17,93,"or possess a house built out of gleaming gold; or ascend up into heaven — and even then we will not believe in your ascent unless you bring us down a book to read!´ Say: ´Glory be to my Lord! Am I anything but a human messenger?´"
  17,94,"Nothing prevents people from having iman when guidance comes to them but the fact that they say, ´Has Allah sent a human being as Messenger?´"
  17,95,"Say: ´If there had been angels on the earth going about in peace, We would have sent down to them an angel from heaven as Messenger.´"
  17,96,"Say: ´Allah is a sufficient witness between me and you. He is certainly aware of and sees His slaves.´"
  17,97,"Whoever Allah guides is truly guided. But as for those He leads astray, you will not find any protectors for them apart from Him. We will gather them on the Day of Rising, flat on their faces, blind, dumb and deaf. Their shelter will be Hell. Whenever the Blaze dies down, We will increase it for them"
  17,98,"That is their repayment for rejecting Our Signs and saying, ´What, when we are bones and crumbled dust, will we then be raised up as a new creation?´"